
Now in case if we want to change the backgournd of the menu which is actually Paper in Menu api and if we want to change the css or override the css then we will use the
classes instead of clasName and then {{ }}   then css role name : classes.customstylename  


classes={{paper:classes.menu}}

menu:{
    backgroundColor:"red",
}

***************************************************************************************************************8
1.import menu and menu item for dropdown

    import Menu from '@material-ui/core/Menu';
     import MenuItem from '@material-ui/core/MenuItem';
     
 2.now we will use usestate to open and close menu
 note    anchorEl    function that returns it. It's used to set the position of the menu  and  is not bulidin i think and import  import React ,{ useState}  from 'react';
                        
             
                            const [anchorEl, setAnchorEl] = React.useState(null);
                            
                            
3.TO OPEN AND CLOSE THE MENU USE THE FOLLOWING FUNCTION 
//THIS WILL THELL WHERE TO TO OPE THE MENU EVENT IS TAKING LOOK AFTER OF IT 
                       
                                         const handleClick = (event) => {
                                              setAnchorEl(event.currentTarget);
                                            };


THIS IS  will close the menu 
                                                           const handleClose = () => {
                                                                                     
                                                              setAnchorEl(null);
                                                                                      };
                                                                                      
                                                                                      
  4.now go to the position or tabs where you want to open the menu on temparey bases write this code the aria-controls="simple-menu" is the id in this case which we will get in 
  the menu opening tag  
  
             aria-controls="simple-menu" aria-haspopup="true" onClick={handleClick}
             
 
 5.now create the meni and menu item 
   <Menu
   //this is the iid
        id="simple-menu"
        anchorEl={anchorEl}
        keepMounted
        
        //anchorEl bu default is false this id will set it true and open the menu 
        open={Boolean(anchorEl)}
        //this will close the menu 
        onClose={handleClose}
      >
      
6.now create the menu item and close it one cliking it 

  <MenuItem onClick={handleClose}>Profile</MenuItem>
  
  7 .now in case if we want to close the menu item for that we will use the MenuList props which we take the javascript object OnMouseLeave inside the main Menu
  
                                                         MenuListProps={{onMouseLeave:handleClose}}
   
   <Menu
        id="simple-menu"
        anchorEl={anchorEl}
        keepMounted
        open={Boolean(anchorEl)}
        onClose={handleClose}
        MenuListProps={{onMouseLeave:handleClose}}
      >
             
       
       
